<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-191-418  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 191 418.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Feb 26 1990 v36 n1798 p24(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Daisy gets 2-month lender reprieve. (Daisy/Cadnetics Inc.)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Daisy/Cadnetix Inc, the unwieldy company formed when Daisy SystemsCorp bought Cadnetix Inc, will receive a two-month reprieve fromits principal secured lender.andP;  Daisy Cadnetix will receive apostponement in enforcement of its loan terms and reduced intereston a bridge loan with $33 million remaining outstanding.andP;  Daisywill also relocate its headquarters from Mountain View, CA toBoulder, CO, site of Cadnetix's headquarters.andP;  The move is seen asa reiteration of Daisy's intent to keep the company together.andO;Other electronic design automation companies have expressedinterest in acquiring Cadnetix, but Daisy will attempt to mergethe two companies and market them as a package.andP;  Daisy/Cadnetix isin some financial trouble: the company reported a net loss of $18million for 1st qtr 1990, and lawsuits by debenture holders areconsidered likely at any time.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Daisy-Cadnetix Inc. (management).andO;Topic:     Financial StabilityDebtMergerReorganizationAutomationDesignFacility Location.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>